article.headline: BC outrebounds West Virginia 40-27
article.linkText: No. 25 Boston College puts away West Virginia
article.story:
MORGANTOWN, West Virginia (Ticker) -- Lisa Macchia came off 
the bench and scored a team-leading 18 points to help 
Boston College (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today) hold off a streaking West Virginia 70-64.

Macchia, a sophomore center, shot 7-for-9 from the floor and
also pulled down nine rebounds in just 25 minutes as the Eagles
(18-5, 8-4 Big East) won their fourth consecutive game to set up
next Saturday's showdown with No. 1 UConn.

Junior guard Jessalyn Deveny led all starters with 17 points on
6-for-13 shooting and also collected a team-leading 12 rebounds
to finish with a double-double for Boston College, which
outrebounded the Mountaineers 40-27.

Kathrin Ress scored 11 points and snatched six rebounds, and
Sarah Marshall chipped in with 11 points of her own, including
4-for-4 from the foul line as the Eagles converted all 10 free
throw attempts over the final five minutes to put the game out
of reach.

Meg Butler scored 17 points and hit three 3-pointers to pace
West Virginia (18-6, 9-3 Big East), which utilized a 9-0 run
late in the first half to cut an early Boston College lead to
just two points by halftime.

Yolanda Paige added 12 points, shot 50 percent (2-for-4) from
behind the 3-point arc, and also dished out a team-leading eight
assists for the Mountainers, who suffered their first loss
since January 10, ending a season-high nine-game winning streak.

Sherell Sowho also chipped in with 11 points and produced three
of the seven steals for West Virgina.
